    Description: Judgement
    Page: 131
By: President George Washington
---
No man is a warmer advocate for proper restraints and wholesome checks in
every department of government than I am; but I have never yet been able to
discover the propriety of placing it absolutely out of the power of men to
render essential services, because a possibility remains of their doing ill.
